  "body": "Hello! I'm writing more comments on our shuffling code in Py-EVM, also peeking yours, and might find these  (potential) issues:\r\n\r\n1. It seems `hashSeed := blake2b.Sum512(seed[:])` only hashed once:\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/d65e2a41571a2739059e797527b7d47c908d9371/beacon-chain/utils/shuffle.go#L19\r\nbut [in the current spec](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/894fb380f39b6249244a35135f31bd409729c371/specs/casper_sharding_v2.1.md), it should be re-hashed in the `for i := 0; i < validatorCount-1; i++` loop.\r\n\r\n2. The check `len(validatorList) > params.GetConfig().MaxValidator`, should be `len(validatorList) > 16777216` for making sure it's in 3-byte size. I don't see you use `remaining` variable in the spec, could you explain it will produce the same result as the spec?\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n",
